This paper discusses the integration of deep learning with knowledge-based systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and databases (cs.DB). The use of long short-term memory (LSTM) artificial neural networks also suggests a focus on natural language processing and sequence modeling, which further supports the likelihood of cs.CL and cs.LG as relevant sub-categories.
